get_individual_p <-function(eta_fo, fo_parFixed){
  
  pk_decay_fo <- list()
  inhibition_fo <- list()
  
  for (i in 1:n_subject){
    pk_decay_ <- exp(eta_fo[i,"eta.pk_decay"] + as.numeric(fo_parFixed[1, 'Est.']))
    inhibition_ <- exp(eta_fo[i,"eta.inhibition_level"] + as.numeric(fo_parFixed[2, 'Est.']))
    #print(i)
    #print(c(pk_decay_,inhibition_))
    pk_decay_fo <- append(pk_decay_fo, pk_decay_)
    inhibition_fo <- append(inhibition_fo, inhibition_)
  }
  
  
  pk_decay_fo_list <- unlist(pk_decay_fo)
  inhibition_fo_list <- unlist(inhibition_fo)
  
  return(list(pk_decay_fo_list, inhibition_fo_list))
}

fo_list <- get_individual_p(eta_fo, fo_parFixed)

foce_list <- get_individual_p(eta_foce, foce_parFixed)
focei_list <- get_individual_p(eta_focei, focei_parFixed)
saem_list <- get_individual_p(eta_saem, saem_parFixed)

mu_foce <- as.numeric(fitting_outcome_foce$parFixed[1:2, 1])
sigma_foce <- unname(as.matrix(fitting_outcome_foce$cov))

mu_saem <- as.numeric(fitting_outcome_saem$parFixed[1:2, 1])
sigma_saem <- unname(as.matrix(fitting_outcome_saem$cov))

sigma_groundtruth <- matrix(c(var_pk_decay, 0, 0, var_inhibition), nrow = 2, ncol = 2)
# Create ellipses
ellipse_fo <- as.data.frame(ellipse(sigma_fo, centre = mu_fo, level = 0.95))
ellipse_foce <- as.data.frame(ellipse(sigma_foce, centre = mu_foce, level = 0.95))
ellipse_saem <- as.data.frame(ellipse(sigma_saem, centre = mu_saem, level = 0.95))
ellipse_groundtruth <- as.data.frame(ellipse(sigma_groundtruth, centre = mu_groundtruth, level = 0.95))

# Add a column to identify the method
ellipse_fo$method <- "FO"
ellipse_foce$method <- "FOCE"
ellipse_saem$method <- "SAEM"
ellipse_groundtruth$method <- "Groundtruth"

# Combine ellipses into one data frame
ellipses <- rbind(ellipse_fo, ellipse_foce, ellipse_saem, ellipse_groundtruth)

# Create a data frame for the center points
centers <- data.frame(
  x = c(mu_fo[1], mu_foce[1], mu_saem[1],  mu_groundtruth[1]),
  y = c(mu_fo[2], mu_foce[2], mu_saem[2], mu_groundtruth[2]),
  method = c("FO", "FOCE", "SAEM", "Groundtruth")
)

# Plot using ggplot2

  geom_path(data = ellipses, aes(x = x, y = y, color = method), size = 1) +

###
simPop_list <- list()
simPop_time_list <- list()
simPop_id_list <- list()

set.seed(123)
n_sampled <- 10
# Generate 100 samples with mean vector (0,0) and covariance matrix
bvn <- mvrnorm(n = n_sampled, 
               mu = mu_pop,
               Sigma = cov_pop)

bvn_linear_scaled <- exp(bvn)

for (i in 1:n_sampled){
  
  pk_decay_ <- bvn_linear_scaled[i,1]
  inhibition_ <- bvn_linear_scaled[i,2]
  sol_output_tag_er_ex <- simu_mtpi_pk_customized(pk_decay_, inhibition_, ev_ex, mod_mtp_modified)
  #
  simPop_list <- append(simPop_list, sol_output_tag_er_ex)
  simPop_time_list <- append(simPop_time_list, time_seq_ex)
  simPop_id_list <- append(simPop_id_list, rep(i, length(time_seq_ex)))
}

simPop_df <- data.frame(ID = unlist(simPop_id_list),
                        TIME = unlist(simPop_time_list),
                        DV= unlist(simPop_list) )

###
simPop_list_data <- list()
simPop_time_list_data <- list()
simPop_id_list_data <- list()

set.seed(123)
n_sampled <- 100
# Generate 100 samples with mean vector (0,0) and covariance matrix
bvn <- mvrnorm(n = n_sampled, 
               mu = mu_pop,
               Sigma = cov_pop)

bvn_linear_scaled <- exp(bvn)

for (i in 1:n_sampled){
  
  pk_decay_ <- bvn_linear_scaled[i,1]
  inhibition_ <- bvn_linear_scaled[i,2]
  sol_output_tag_er_data <- simu_mtpi_pk(pk_decay_, inhibition_)
  #
  simPop_list_data <- append(simPop_list_data, sol_output_tag_er_data)
  simPop_time_list_data <- append(simPop_time_list_data, time_seq)
  simPop_id_list_data <- append(simPop_id_list_data, rep(i, length(time_seq)))
}

simPop_df_data <- data.frame(ID = unlist(simPop_id_list_data),
                             TIME = unlist(simPop_time_list_data),
                             DV= unlist(simPop_list_data) )

# Compute statistics by TIME
stats_df_data  <- aggregate(DV ~ TIME, data = simPop_df_data, FUN = function(x) {
  c(mean = mean(x),
    median = median(x),
    q05 = quantile(x, 0.05),
    q95 = quantile(x, 0.95))
})

# Convert the results to a proper dataframe
stats_df_data  <- data.frame(
  TIME = stats_df_data $TIME,
  mean = stats_df_data $DV[,1],
  median = stats_df_data $DV[,2],
  q05 = stats_df_data $DV[,3],
  q95 = stats_df_data $DV[,4]
)


p_gen_additionalExpo_data  <- ggplot(stats_df_data , aes(x = TIME)) +
  geom_point(data= origData,aes( x=TIME,y=DV)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = mean, color = "Mean")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = median, color = "Median")) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = q05, ymax = q95, fill = "5-95% CI"), alpha = 0.2) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Mean" = "blue", "Median" = "red")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("5-95% CI" = "gray")) +
  labs(x = "Time", y = "DV",
       title = "time course of statistics (mean, median, 5-95%CI) of simulations from vitural population with observed data") +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = ""),
         fill = guide_legend(title = "")) +
  theme_minimal()

ggplotly(p_gen_additionalExpo_data)
